content = "Measure the angle from the horizontal lines on the latitude measure to the sundial pointer. The lines will act as references.

The horizontal line indicates 0 degrees, and each following thick lines indicates 30 and 60 degrees. The vertical line indicates 90 degrees.

To get the latitude, estimate where the pointer falls on the latitude measure. In the example, the latitude is probably around 15 degrees."
